President Cyril Ramaphosa briefing media about the country's first case of Covid-19 Coronavirus at Waterkloof Airforce base in Pretoria. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has called for consolidated reports from his Cabinet as the country experiences rapidly rising coronavirus cases. An urgent cabinet meeting will be held on Sunday to discuss the measures implemented to deal with the pandemic. The number of confirmed cases in South Africa has now risen to 38. READ: Coronavirus cases in South Africa rise to 38 This is an increase of 14 from Friday including the youngest patient being a 14-year-old who travelled to Dubai and the US. Seven of the new cases are in Gauteng, 6 in the Western Cape, and one in KwaZulu-Natal. All patients have returned from travelling outside the country. Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize says he's concerned about the increasing number of infections. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.